cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the use of technology, specifically data mining techniques, for improving healthcare management through the analysis of electronic health records (EHRs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with the storage and retrieval of large amounts of patient data. The use of machine learning algorithms for modeling EHRs suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Finally, cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) could be a possible category as the paper may touch upon issues related to the privacy and security of patient data.
